They thronged Mpilo Central Hospital, the announced venue of the exercise, to try their hand in the programme only to be turned away, the State-run Chronicle newspaper reports. Zimbabwe's Ministry of Health has since dismissed the advertisement as a fake. In a tweet, the ministry said online applications to the programme closed on August 31 and had not been extended as announced in the advertisement.

